Package: scNPM
Type: Package
Title: scNPM: Integrating Protein Interactomes with Single-Cell Network Propensity Matching for Identifying Heterogeneous Regulatory Pathway
Version: 1.0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      given = "Tao",
      family = "Liu",
      email = "25210690190@m.fudan.edu.cn",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: We introduce scNPM, a computational framework designed to construct and compare heterogeneous gene
    regulatory networks across biological conditions. By applying a network propensity model to single-cell transcriptomic
    data, scNPM matches comparable cell clusters between AMD and healthy retinas. This enables the identification of
    cell-cluster-specific regulatory edges that are otherwise obscured by cellular heterogeneity. Through integration of a
    protein-protein interactome, scNPM prioritizes these context-specific interactions. Applied to AMD, scNPM reconstructed
    the heterogeneous regulatory landscape, nominated novel candidate driver genes, and proposed mechanistic hypotheses
    for pathogenesis specific to distinct cell types, demonstrating its power to generate actionable insights from complex data.
